### Topics Covered

#### Multiple Linear Regression

* Using multiple features to make predictions.
* Understanding how different inputs contribute to the output.

#### Vectorization

* Performing computations efficiently using vectors and matrices.
* Reducing the need for loops and improving performance.

#### Gradient Descent

* Optimizing model parameters by minimizing the cost function.
* Understanding the role of the learning rate.

#### Feature Scaling

* Scaling features to similar ranges.
* Helping gradient descent converge faster.

#### Checking Convergence

* Monitoring whether gradient descent is approaching the minimum cost.
* Using cost values to evaluate learning progress.

#### Choosing the Learning Rate

* Small learning rate = slower convergence.
* Large learning rate = risk of overshooting the minimum.

#### Feature Engineering

* Creating useful features from existing data.
* Improving model performance through better representations.

#### Polynomial Regression

* Modeling non-linear relationships using polynomial features.
* Extending linear regression to fit more complex patterns.

